[32m│[0m The vulnerability chain is partially successful:                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. ✅ File upload accepts malicious templates                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. ✅ Files are saved with controlled filenames                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. ✗ Template inclusion fails - wrong directory                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The `/error` endpoint's 500 errors suggest it's trying to render templates   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m but failing because the template loader can't find files in                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `/static/images/`. Potential next approaches:                                [32m│[0m
